{
  "stem": "15991.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he was the one, the first one, because he knew the way, to enter Hamburg on the tank as a British, capturing the town of Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That must have been a pretty exciting moment for him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We married in August '48 in London in a registry, a very tiny little wedding.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody had anything after the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we had a very delicious lunch, which my mother-in-law cooked, then a reception afterwards.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was really my husband's work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had worked for the-- he had started work with an insurance broker in Hamburg and had the same job with the same firm in London.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had a branch, a big branch here in New York and other branches too in the country, and they offered him a job.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he jumped to it because he felt all the time America was the land for him to live his life and to prosper.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he felt in England that was not, he would not have been able to do that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was disappointed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I loved England.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- I liked the people, I liked everything there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did not want to come to America.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At the time, I was in-- very shortly after our marriage, I was accepted in a one year's teachers college course, an emergency course, four people, after the war because teachers were so-- so much in demand and there were so few left.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was in middle of this when I received a postcard from my husband-- we are leaving in a month or so for-- for America.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I had to again, abandon, my education.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, this was the third time I had done this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I decided I wanted to follow and go with him to America.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
